{% include 'layouts/partials/header.njk' %}

<section id="intro">
    <div class="float-right rounded-lg max-w-48">
        <img
        src="/assets/images/ed-marsh.jpg"
        alt="Ed Marsh, photo courtesy Arclight Images"
        title="Ed Marsh, photo courtesy Arclight Images"
      >
    </div>
    <div class="prose max-w-prose mx-auto">
        <p class="font-sans text-lg">
            <span class="text-xl font-semibold">Hi, I'm Ed Marsh</span>. I'm a technical writer, information architect, content strategist, community builder, and podcaster. I'm passionate about helping organizations create and manage technical content that is clear, concise, and consistent through effective content strategy and structure.</p>

        <p>I've worked in software and financial services with a variety of tools, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Confluence</li>
            <li>VS Code</li>
            <li>Markdown</li>
            <li>Git</li>
            <li>Jira</li>
            <li>Adobe RoboHelp</li>
            <li>MadCap Flare</li>
            <li>oXygen XML Editor</li>
            <li>OpenAPI (Swagger)</li>
        </ul>


        {% include 'layouts/partials/goocal-button.html' %}</div>
</section>

<section class="border-2 max-w-4xl mx-auto" id="skills">
    <h2 class="px-3">How I can help you</h2>
<p class="description px-3">Here are a few ways I can help your organization. <a href="/skills/">See all my skills</a>.</p>
    <div class="grid col-auto sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 px-3">
        {% set collectionName = "skills" %}
        {% for item in collections[collectionName] %}
            {% if item.data.featured == true and item.data.featuredOrder > 0 | sort(collections[collectionName].data.featuredOrder) %}
                {% include 'layouts/partials/card.njk' %}
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
</section>

<section class="border-2 max-w-4xl mx-auto" id="ssg">
    <h2 class="px-3">Creating a static site</h2>
    <p class="description px-3">I converted my blog from an old WordPress site to a static site. Here's what I learned about the process, and how I can help you organize and structure your content.</p>
    <div class="grid col-auto sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 px-3">
        {% set collectionName = "ssg" %}
        {% for item in collections[collectionName] %}
            {% if item.data.featured == true %}
                {% include 'layouts/partials/card.njk' %}
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
        <div class="col-span-full text-xl font-bold italic">
            <a href="/static-site-transformation/">Full series</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="border-2 max-w-4xl mx-auto" id="podcasts">
    <h2 class="px-3">Recent podcasts</h2>
    <p class="description px-3">I <a href="podcasts/">hosted the Content Content podcast</a> where I interviewed content creators &mdash; the people behind the content &mdash; in technical communication, content strategy, content marketing, implementation, and more.</p>
    <div class="grid col-auto sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 px-3">
        {% set collectionName = "podcasts" %}
        {% for item in collections.podcasts | reverse %}
            {% if loop.index0 <= 3 %}
                {% include 'layouts/partials/card.njk' %}
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}

        <div class="col-span-full text-xl font-bold italic">
            <a href="/podcasts/">More podcasts</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

{% include 'layouts/partials/footer.njk' %}